4 Section 1-6-103. A. Juvenile court records and Department of
5 Human Services agency records pertaining to a child may be
6 inspected, and their contents shall be disclosed, without a court
7 order to the following persons upon showing of proper credentials
8 and pursuant to their lawful duties:
9 1. The court having the child currently before it in any
10 proceeding pursuant to this title, any district court or tribal
11 court to which such proceedings may be transferred, employees and
12 officers of the court in the performance of their duties,
13 including, but not limited to, guardians ad litem appointed by the
14 court, and court-appointed special advocates;
15 2. A district attorney, United States Attorney, or Attorney
16 General of this or another state and the employees of such offices
17 in the course of their official duties pursuant to this title or
18 the prosecution of crimes against children, or upon their request
19 in their official capacity as advisor in a grand jury proceeding;
20 3. The attorney representing a child who is the subject of a
21 proceeding pursuant to the provisions of this title or other
22 proceeding where child custody or visitation is at issue;
23 4. Employees of juvenile bureaus in the course of their
24 official duties pursuant to this title, and employees of the
