3 B. In addition to the persons listed in subsection A of this
4 section, juvenile court records may be inspected, and their
5 contents shall be disclosed, without a court order to the following
6 persons upon showing of proper credentials and pursuant to their
7 lawful duties:
8 1. Employees of court-appointed special advocate programs, as
9 defined in Section 1-1-105 of this title, in the course of their
10 official duties pertaining to recruiting, screening, training,
11 assigning cases, supervising, and supporting volunteers in their
12 roles as guardian ad litem pursuant to Section 1-4-306 of this
13 title;
14 2. Members of postadjudication review boards established
15 pursuant to the provisions of Section 1116.2 of Title 10 of the
16 Oklahoma Statutes, the Child Death Review Board, and
17 multidisciplinary personnel. In addition to juvenile court
18 records, members of such postadjudication review boards may
19 inspect, without a court order, information that includes, but is
20 not limited to:
21 a. psychological and medical records,
22 b. placement history and information, including the
23 names and addresses of foster parents,
24 c. family assessments,
(Floor Amendments Only) Date and Time Filed:
Untimely Amendment Cycle Extended Secondary Amendment

1 d. treatment or service plans, and
2 e. school records;
3 3. The Department of Human Services or other public or private
4 agency or individual having court-ordered custody or physical
5 custody pursuant to Department placement of the child, or
6 conducting a child abuse or neglect investigation of the child who
7 is the subject of the record. In addition to juvenile court
8 records, employees of the Department may inspect, without a court
9 order and upon a showing of proper credentials and pursuant to
10 their lawful duties, information that includes, but is not limited
11 to:
12 a. psychological and medical records, and
13 b. nondirectory education records;
14 4. The child who is the subject of the record and the parents,
15 legal guardian, custodian, or foster parent of such child; and
16 5. A person authorized by the court to conduct bona fide
17 research, provided such research may not publish the names or
18 identities of parents, children, or other persons contained in the
19 records.
20 C. In addition to the persons and entities named in subsection
21 A of this section, Department of Human Services agency records may
22 be inspected, and their contents shall be disclosed, without a
23 court order to the following persons upon showing of proper
24 credentials and pursuant to their lawful duties:
